            <tr class=3D"replica" name=3D"s1">
             <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">There were many =
historic aspects of <b>Kamala Harris</b>=E2=80=99s candidacy: her gender, h=
er race, her midsummer anointment. But perhaps most jaw-dropping was the in=
credible success of her fundraising machine, which amassed more than $1 bil=
lion in donations, an unprecedented sum that was tangible, undeniable proof=
 of her campaign=E2=80=99s momentum and enthusiasm. <br/><br/>But within 24=
 hours of her landslide loss, as anyone who received an election night text=
 from =E2=80=9CBarack Obama=E2=80=9D probably sussed out, the campaign was =
in the red. Today, word started to trickle out that the campaign has essent=
ially burned its entire cash reserve, and is still fundraising to cover pot=
ential debts, an equally stunning data point for an operation that had as m=
uch as <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1=
lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUQ2NTc2VqUlN6LTdkTlQ3YjV2Zz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvb=
S9jY2FkZWxhZ28vc3RhdHVzLzE4NTQzNDI2NjcyNTExODc3OTU_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVRoZStC=
ZXN0KyUyNitUaGUrQnJpZ2h0ZXN0Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTElMkY3JTJGMjQlMjlcdTA=
wMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMm=
EiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoxOTY4MDA3fQ/5a69c06e1e520df960dc1ef5d24882f5a493f64a88263a=
829c713d93d9f35b42" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight=
:bold" class=3D"sdf">$118 million</a></u> in cash on hand as of October 16.=
 <br/><br/>Contributions are still trickling in, according to a D.N.C. sour=
ce, who said the campaign=E2=80=99s total debt will almost certainly be low=
er once all the incoming money is accounted for. (They have until December =
15 to submit their fourth-quarter campaign finance report.) Nevertheless, I=
=E2=80=99m told by campaign sources, the Harris camp is now reaching out to=
 Democratic groups to sell her vast dataset of supporter emails and phone n=
umbers to offset those losses=E2=80=94a common tactic among both Democrats =
and Republicans. (Yes, <b>Obama</b> did it too=E2=80=A6) How valuable is Ha=
rris=E2=80=99s supporter list? Given donor fatigue at both the small-dollar=
 and high-dollar donor levels, any buyer may find them already strip-mined =
of much of their value. <br/><br/>The Harris
campaign is pursuing other tactics, too. It has already launched a post-ele=
ction fundraising campaign on KamalaHarris.com called the =E2=80=9CHarris F=
ight Fund,=E2=80=9D whose stated mission is to maintain staffing in states =
where Senate and House races are still too close to call. Texts from =E2=80=
=9C<b>Tim Walz</b>=E2=80=9D were still requesting $40 for the Harris Fight =
Fund a full <i>two days</i> after the polls closed. Whatever donations =E2=
=80=9CTim=E2=80=9D or any of the other solicitors collect goes to the Democ=
ratic National Committee, to offset the campaign debt they=E2=80=99ll inher=
it. <br/><br/>These financial pressures are likely to factor into December=
=E2=80=99s election for D.N.C. chairperson. But first, the organization is =
likely to lay off some staff, as is typical following an election. Current =
chair <b>Jaime</b> <b>Harrison</b> is expected to step down, leaving his su=
ccessor to somehow refortify the group=E2=80=99s tattered balance sheet=E2=
=80=94not an easy job when many are questioning the efficacy of text outrea=
ch
and email, not to mention the efficacy of the Democratic Party itself. =E2=
=80=9CThe chair is going to have to spend 75 percent of their time fundrais=
ing in an ecosystem where donors are fatigued, and they=E2=80=99re going to=
 be in deep financial trouble,=E2=80=9D said a former D.N.C. official. (A s=
pokesperson for the D.N.C. declined to comment.)<br/></td>
